      "Alright, here's what we settled on:\r\n* `pluck` will accept both `=> true` and `=> [:a, :b, :c]` (i.e. we use arrays to specify the union of one or more paths).\r\n* We will automatically recurse into arrays.\r\n* We will, at some point in the future, introduce `r.number`, `r.array`, etc. and people can use them in paths passed to e.g. `has_fields` or `with_fields` to get schema enforcement."
